sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM final_grades 
WHERE course_code = '61603' AND grade < 'C';

external_knowledge:
- "top students" refers to students who received an 'A' grade and have an average of at least 80 marks;
- "overall marks" correspond to the sum of all marks obtained in the course;
- "outstanding performance" in this context means the total marks obtained, with higher values representing better performance;
- "commendable average" in this context means an average of 80 or higher marks, reflecting a high level of performance.

sql:
SELECT students.student_name, final_grades.grade
FROM students
INNER JOIN final_grades ON students.reg_no = final_grades.reg_no;

